The paper proposes algorithms for efficiently finding the best match with respect to the inner product, which is a fundamental problem in many areas of computer science such as information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). The proposed algorithms use tree data structures, which are commonly used in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.DB.
